First of all, my apologies if my questions are out of context for this group. I only get these kind of questions and I don't know where else to ask. Please let me know if I am out of context. Thanks!

Coming to my question -

I've been reading Yoga vasishta. I see that in some stories when a person dies with a strong desire, he becomes that in his next life, enabling him to fulfill that desire. But eventually, after many lifetimes, he comes back to doing tapas once again.

I am a homemaker. There is some longing in me to become a career woman(or rather to be known as a career woman). So if I focus my energy in fulfilling that desire, experience whatever there is to be experienced, hopefully not catch any additional desires during that process, and finally fulfill that need in me - is that time and energy well spent?

I mean, is fulfilling a desire a wise way of getting rid of that desire??


